author: PerreoEnLaDisco
body: I can write, I just have a different world perspective than you due to the nature of my previous job. Generally seems that service members have a much less myopic worldview and don’t generally have an issue with speaking bluntly, instead of beating around the bush and searching for “acceptable” worlds like non-service members do. Probably has something to do with a common wide breadth of experience, from shit hot embassy TDY treatment to sleeping in the dirt and shitting in holes in undeveloped countries.
